{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "lxxe:job.26",
    "translationId": "lxxe",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 26,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 26",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 26 in Brenton's English Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.26.1",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 26:1",
      "text": "But Job answered and said,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.26.2",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 26:2",
      "text": "To whom dost thou attach thyself, or whom art thou going to assist? is it not he that has much strength, and he who has a strong arm?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.26.3",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 26:3",
      "text": "To whom hast thou given counsel? is it not to him who has all wisdom? whom wilt thou follow? is it not one who has the greatest power?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.26.4",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 26:4",
      "text": "To whom hast thou uttered words? and whose breath is it that has come forth from thee?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.26.5",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 26:5",
      "text": "Shall giants be born from under the water and the inhabitants thereof?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.26.6",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 26:6",
      "text": "Hell is naked before him, and destruction has no covering.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.26.7",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 26:7",
      "text": "He stretches out the north wind upon nothing, and he upon nothing hangs the earth;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.26.8",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 26:8",
      "text": "binding water in his clouds, and the cloud is not rent under it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.26.9",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 26:9",
      "text": "He keeps back the face of his throne, stretching out his cloud upon it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.26.10",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 26:10",
      "text": "He has encompassed the face of the water by an appointed ordinance, until the end of light and darkness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.26.11",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 26:11",
      "text": "The pillars of heaven are prostrate and astonished at his rebuke.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.26.12",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 26:12",
      "text": "He has calmed the sea with his might, and by his wisdom the whale has been overthrown.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.26.13",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 26:13",
      "text": "And the barriers of heaven fear him, and by a command he has slain the apostate dragon.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:job.26.14",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 26,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 26:14",
      "text": "Behold, these are parts of his way; and we will hearken to him at the least intimation of his word: but the strength of his thunder who knows, when he shall employ it?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
